wfIisisGeneralDelete.name: wfIisisGeneralDelete
wfIisisGeneralDelete.description: 'This value determines whether I-ISIS is configured'

wfIisisGeneralDisable.name: wfIisisGeneralDisable
wfIisisGeneralDisable.description: 'The administrative status of I-ISIS in the router. The value 'enabled' denotes that the I-ISIS Process is active on at least one interface; 'disabled' disables it on all interfaces.'

wfIisisRouterId.name: wfIisisRouterId
wfIisisRouterId.description: This value contains the system ID of this Intermediate System.

wfIisisVersion.name: wfIisisVersion
wfIisisVersion.description: This read-only parameter identifies the version number of the IS-IS protocol to which this node conforms to.

wfIisisRouterType.name: wfIisisRouterType
wfIisisRouterType.description: This value determines whether this system is L1 only router L2 only router or L1-L2 IS.

wfIisisSpfHoldDown.name: wfIisisSpfHoldDown
wfIisisSpfHoldDown.description: Hold Down Timer for the SPF (in seconds). The SPF will run at most once per hold down timer value. A value of 0 means no hold down.

wfIisisPrimaryLogMask.name: wfIisisPrimaryLogMask
wfIisisPrimaryLogMask.description: A parameter to specify which I-ISIS log messages should be logged. This will only effect the Primary I-ISIS gate. Each bit represents a message as defined below. A 1 in that bit location means to log it and a 0 means not to put that log message in the log. Changing this value will NOT restart I-ISIS, but will take effct immediately(if there are any messages to be logged. bit 31 bit 0 +---------------------------------------+ | | +---------------------------------------+ bit0 Trace Messages bit1 INFO Level messages bit2 debug level messages bit3 I-ISIS interface state change messages bit4 Nbr state changes bit5 self-origination of LSA's bit6 receipt of new LSA's bit7 changes to I-ISIS`s Routing Table bit8 Bad LS requests, Ack's, or updates bit9 receipt of less recent LSA's bit10 receipt of more recent self-originated LSA's bit11 receipt of MAxAge LSA's (i.e. LSA's being flushed) bit12 - 31 reserved

wfIisisMaximumPath.name: wfIisisMaximumPath
wfIisisMaximumPath.description: Maximum number of equal cost paths allowed for a network installed by OSPF.

wfIisisMaxAreas.name: wfIisisMaxAreas
wfIisisMaxAreas.description: This value defines the maximum allowable number of areas addresses for the domain that this router exists in.

wfIisisNumL1Lsps.name: wfIisisNumL1Lsps
wfIisisNumL1Lsps.description: Number of L2 LSPS stored in the database

wfIisisNumL2Lsps.name: wfIisisNumL2Lsps
wfIisisNumL2Lsps.description: Number of L2 LSPS stored in the database

wfIisisCksumIsPdus.name: wfIisisCksumIsPdus
wfIisisCksumIsPdus.description: This value indicates whether ISIS PDUs will carry a checksum.

wfIisisL1LspPassword.name: wfIisisL1LspPassword
wfIisisL1LspPassword.description: This assigns a password such that only L1 Lsps with the matching password will be accepted. All L1 Lsps generated by this system will contain this string in the password option.

wfIisisL2LspPassword.name: wfIisisL2LspPassword
wfIisisL2LspPassword.description: This assigns a password such that only L2 Lsps with the matching password will be accepted. All L2 Lsps generated by this system will contain this string in the password option.

wfIisisAreaAddr.name: wfIisisAreaAddr
wfIisisAreaAddr.description: This Assigns the area address for this router. This field must be filled in. If the user doesn't enter a value, then assign 0x470005. Site Manager must force the user to enter at least a 3-byte value for this field.

wfIisisAreaAddrAlias1.name: wfIisisAreaAddrAlias1
wfIisisAreaAddrAlias1.description: This Assigns the first area address alias for this router. This field does no have to be filled in, but if the user tries to enter a value, Site Manager must make sure that it is at least 3-bytes in length.

wfIisisAreaAddrAlias2.name: wfIisisAreaAddrAlias2
wfIisisAreaAddrAlias2.description: This Assigns the second area address alias for this router. This field does no have to be filled in, but if the user tries to enter a value, Site Manager must make sure that it is at least 3-bytes in length.

wfIisisL1LspDbOverLoads.name: wfIisisL1LspDbOverLoads

wfIisisL2LspDbOverLoads.name: wfIisisL2LspDbOverLoads
wfIisisL2LspDbOverLoads.description: Number of times the L2Lsp Database Overload event has been generated.

wfIisisNearestL2Is.name: wfIisisNearestL2Is
wfIisisNearestL2Is.description: This is the ID of the nearest L2 system in this area.

wfIisisMaxLSPGenerationInterval.name: wfIisisMaxLSPGenerationInterval

wfIisisAgePend.name: wfIisisAgePend

wfIisisIfHelloMtuSize.description: Configure Hello MTU size per I-ISIS interface This parameter has the following values/meanings: 1 - Use the MTU specified by IP 2 - Use the MTU of ethernet, regardless of what IP says > 2 - Use this value as the actual MTU.
